		<p>If this ever gets built [July 2009: it probably won't. They changed their name to Pursu Mobility a few months back and pulled down the news/discussion boards so now there is no hint that anything is happening. They were using technology from Carver but now they've gone under.], I want one! As much as I like the Lean Machine, it doesn't look tough or sporty like this does. This would sell if ...</p>
		<p>In August 2007 after a long period of silence on their web site, they announced that they had secured $6 million of funding which will presumably get them a nice prototype which they can then use to get the real money required for a factory, dealer network and advertising. The track record of start-up automobile companies in the developed world is basically 100% failure so I wish one of the big four Japanese motorcycle companies or BMW would take this on as they already have the engineering expertise and capital to fully develop it but more importantly, have a dealer network and brand recognition that would make people feel comfortable about buying it knowing they will later be able to get it serviced and that a market will likely exist for second-hand machines.</p>
